**SC-8: Encryption in Transit**

**SSP Description (from Day 50):** HTTPS enforced — HTTP redirects to HTTPS. TLS 1.2 minimum. ACM certificate. MySQL connection from EC2 to RDS requires TLS.

**Implementation Verification:**

*HTTPS enforcement:*
Apache Tomcat server.xml configuration: HTTP connector on port 8080 includes a redirect to port 8443 (HTTPS). The EC2 security group does not permit inbound port 80 from the internet — the redirect is handled at the application layer for any connection that reaches Tomcat directly, but internet-facing traffic on port 80 is dropped at the security group before reaching the application.

Recommendation: confirming the WAF/ALB layer handles the HTTP-to-HTTPS redirect at the perimeter (before reaching EC2) provides defense-in-depth for the redirect enforcement.

*TLS configuration:*
ACM certificate status: Issued. Domain: [openmrs-domain]. Expiration: [date]. ACM auto-renewal enabled. CloudWatch alarm configured to alert 30 days before expiration — this was identified as a gap in Day 50 and has now been configured. Alarm name: [openmrs-cert-expiry-30d]; alarm state: OK.

TLS protocol: Tomcat SSL configuration specifies sslEnabledProtocols="TLSv1.2,TLSv1.3" — TLS 1.0 and 1.1 are not included. Cipher suite configured to prefer ECDHE-based key exchange for forward secrecy.

*RDS TLS enforcement:*
OpenMRS database connection string in runtime.properties: driverClassName=com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver with useSSL=true and requireSSL=true. RDS parameter group: rds.force_ssl=1 — connections without TLS are rejected at the database level, providing enforcement at both ends of the connection.

**No discrepancies found.**

**Verification Evidence:** ACM certificate console screenshot; Tomcat server.xml configuration (redacted to remove sensitive values); CloudWatch alarm for certificate expiration; RDS parameter group showing force_ssl=1; OpenMRS runtime.properties connection string (redacted).

